    <scopecontent id="ref8">
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>Burnett's Wheat Fan Instructions was printed in Salem, Virginia in September 1851,
                and it contains directions on how to use C.M. Burnett's patent beveled wheat fan.
                The document is a one page sheet of directions for using the wheat fan. The
                directions are split out by crop type and are for wheat, oats, corn, clover, flax,
                and timothy seed.</p>
    </scopecontent>
